g.text: Drama: Look at her! Her hands, her nails, the cigarette... Every second you stall, you become more entangled in this spider's *web of lies*. Arrest her immediately!
She probably didn't make the god damn call either -- why would she? She was too busy abusing morphine and *cocainum!* Arrest her immediately!
Rhetoric: Shush. I can't hear what she's saying.
Physical Instrument: Let the miss speak. She's tall and thin and tired -- a twig trying so hard not to break...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why *did* you waste our time then?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Because of the Hardies -- I couldn't just dispense with them, they were only trying to help me." She looks at her feet. "Out of the shit I'd gotten into."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It was a mistake." She winces. "I'm sorry for wasting your time."
Volition: C'mon. She lied through her teeth. And you know it.
You: "What's the RCM's involvement with the Moralintern got to do with this?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I know." She looks down for a moment, hiding her eyes behind her bangs. "For what it's worth, I'm sorry. For all of this, for wasting your time."
Kim Kitsuragi: Until the lieutenant loses patience: "What does our *limited cooperation* with the MI have to do with this?"
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""You share a database with them. Yo..."]
You: "Why did you call the cops if you're hiding?"
You: "Why didn't you run away from here? As a matter of fact -- why are you here now?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "11.30 to 12.15. I don't know the exact time. Around midnight."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She throws it away and immediately proceeds to light another one.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "No..." She smiles nervously. The beads of her teeth shine.
Suggestion: Still -- there is something there. She won't tell you now.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She said she'd take care of this. It's what she does, you know. Take care of things. I helped her get the body to the bathroom -- we used a belt to pull him up under the shower. To keep him upright."
Suggestion: What are you trying to be -- tactful? She wouldn't mind. Go on then...
Jump to: [Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): ""He was heavy. I pushed him off and..."]
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "About twenty, yes. Ruby explained it would make the blood... you know what it does." She looks at the ground. Then raises her light brown eyes to meet yours.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She blinks, without averting her gaze.
Visual Calculus: This is concurrent with your doubts -- at the autopsy -- about the colouring being...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Because life is hell, officer," she finds refuge in her cigarette. It's thin, but it's something.
You: "Okay. I'd like you to answer some other questions, miss." (Conclude.)
Rhetoric: It's not one of respect. You may want to add a clever *retort* to this one.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant gives you a sideways glance.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She takes a healthy -- nay, *giant* healthy -- drag of her menthol cigarette, waiting for what's next to come.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Last week. Angus and Titus's brother -- I think he's called Tibbs -- took care of it." She takes a drag.
Drama: Stop staring and say something dramatic and professional!
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I *did* -- I also had a side job selling insurance that I was really good at. Got picked up by a bank. *Competitive intelligence*, they called it."
Half Light: Tighten it. You've got her.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Okay, yes -- it's not." She's cornered. "It's not my name."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I didn't show up to a rendezvous. They don't take that *lightly*." She rushes to explain: "I didn't show up because I was afraid they'd... do something to me. The job was finished -- I'm just a liability now."
Empathy: She fears an arrest right here and now. This has been an awful turn of events for her.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She nods. "It was a sentimental thing. I wanted to be more *me* here. This time. So I used my nickname."
Shivers: Long, spindly arms are spinning the buoy around, turning it, inspecting it like a magic eight-ball, trying to find a way to snap it open...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I haven't said it aloud in such a long time... that name." She shakes her head.
Rhetoric: She's filling dead air. Can't stand the silence.
You: (Turn to the lieutenant.) "Kim, why have we not *arrested* her yet?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "There may be grounds here... At least for an extended detention."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Klaasje..." she repeats with a pained smile on her face, her back pressed against the railing.
Drama: That's right. Stern and merciless now, STERN AND MERCILESS as we reel her in.
That's right, gang. Stern and merciless now -- STERN AND MERCILESS as we reel her in.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good." He turns to her, the cuffs still in his hand. "What -- in your relationship -- made you think she's romantically interested in you?"

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A little. I was flattered, you know. But then I had to let her off and it was *not* easy. I came to regret being friendly with her." She looks at her feet. "We maybe kissed. Nothing more."
Volition: It also has startlingly little to do with arresting her, you suddenly realize...
You: "I don't understand. Ruby's a woman, right? It's a *woman's* name."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I know what this sounds like. That's why I didn't want to tell you before." She raises her eyes to meet yours. "But she *knew* what had happened -- when I came downstairs."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "And more." She nods. "I made the mistake of confiding in her -- I told her I was on the run. She started *protecting* me. It became an unhealthy relationship."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Did you hear or see the shooter in the course of this?"
You: "You're a flight risk -- and I've already told you're a *suspect* in a murder investigation, remember?"
Half Light: Waiting for your teeth and talons to cut into...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "*Everything* could change." She looks around. "This city, the extradition rules... The people after me could be in jail. Or maybe Revachol..." She falls silent.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I can do this on my own. She's not an immediate flight risk. See you tomorrow morning, officer. Downstairs, at the Whirling-in-Rags."
"I can do this on my own. She's not an immediate flight risk. See you tomorrow morning, officer. Downstairs, at the Whirling-in-Rags. Or outside your shack."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I know, but..." She doesn't know what to say.
Drama: The political gambit has failed.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I think you meant to say *bitch* there."
You: It doesn't matter. Better not to mention it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's okay. Tell us as much as you're comfortable with." He waits for her to continue.
Volition: ...or maybe you should take her to the station? For safekeeping. She *lied* to you. And she's a flight risk.
Drama: Who... what... Dear god, you've been lied to! She could have killed her lover and lied to everyone! She's not *candid* at all, she's smoke and mirrors and will-o-wisps!
Who... what? Dear lord, you've been lied to. She could have killed her lover and lied to everyone! She's not the most *faire and juste* at all, she's smoke and mirrors and will-o-wisps!

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I promise I will be right here all the time -- nights too. I'll help you *any* way I can in this investigation and I *will* be at Station 41 in six weeks." She repeats. "I promise."
You: "What's going on? What did you do?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Industrial espionage. I joined a business collective with the intention of betraying them. I did my job well enough to be asked to do it again."
You: "Is this part of why Oranje is a *bad memory* for you?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "That doesn't really work, does it?" She has almost devoured the cigarette she lit. She looks at it sadly. "Not without a drink to wash it down..."
You: "That's..." (Shake your head.) "Not easy to deal with."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Yeah, it was a real *motherfucker*... ouch..." She looks down. Her cigarette has singed her fingers.
"Yeah, it was a real *motherfucker*." She immediately lights another one.
Perception (Sight): She's forgotten about her cigarette. The butt has burned right down to her fingernails...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She looks down with a wince. Her cigarette has singed her fingers.
Logic: Coming up with a theory. She said Ruby *knew* something was wrong before she said anything. How come? It was loud downstairs, she couldn't have heard the shot...
Volition: It is ominous -- you already coming up with theories that put the blame on someone other than Klaasje.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Well, Ruby said let's talk upstairs. I showed her the room... I've known these people since December, they know my situation. That I can't leave a paper trail. Ruby was the first one I told..."
Hand/Eye Coordination: Another hit. The lieutenant looks at you -- in acknowledgement.
Logic: He was a serviceman -- he must have had a gun. Somewhere, lying around. Close to her hand...
Electrochemistry: All kinds of *crazy* things happen when drugs are involved... sweet, sweet drugs.
Physical Instrument: She has the training for it. Two, maybe three years of self defence? Her body is hard and lean underneath that jump suit...
Volition: Look who's waking up from a thousand years of sleep!
You: Better not start on this.
You: "You've lied to me about this bullet before. When I said he was *shot*? You said you're *confused*."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Or... I don't know anything anymore. All I do is wait here." She looks at the table.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Like what?" She waits, her light brown eyes wandering... over the floor... over your face...
You: "I don't think so. Why did you do it?"

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You have to understand -- the people around here... No one was making the call, and he kept rotting. And then they picked his clothes off. And that little fucker threw stones at him..."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Last week. Angus and Titus's brother -- I think he's called Tibbs -- took care of it." She takes a drag. "I told you I'm a horrible girl. I told you things break around me."
Logic: Interesting. Why did this Ruby go through so much trouble -- to hide something someone *else* did? Look into this later!
Kim Kitsuragi: "Uhm..." The lieutenant glances at you -- then at the door.
Esprit de Corps: He's thinking -- *are* we done here?
Encyclopedia: That *is* the Emergencies Desk number...
Drama: Anyone could know that, sire. By looking around and calling the desk. I don't believe a single word she says!
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why would they do that?"
Visual Calculus: The light refracts. She takes out her lighter.

Esprit de Corps: You almost say the words, then stop -- the lieutenant is off somewhere, 28 kilometres from here, probably reading the *manual* for incarceration. The one he *knows how to use*. Come back and say this with Kim here; you can't handle it without him.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She's silent for a second -- as if looking into herself for certainty. Then, in a hushed voice, she says...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I mean romantically." He turns to her, the cuffs still in his hand. "What exactly in your relationship with Ruby made you think she's romantically interested in you?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "And you led her on?" The lieutenant narrows his eyes.
Physical Instrument: Well, I'll be damned! That's one more thing we know about the world!
Electrochemistry: She's not really sure. It *was* right above the bed -- she could have seen all sorts of things from there.
Volition: Her! Stop letting her distract you.
Logic: Actually -- this murder did have *a little* to do with her.
Half Light: You *are*. This is not the end of this.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Thank you." She cradles herself for warmth. "Thank you. You won't regret it."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I will escort you to the motor carriage outside, miss."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You said there was a secret route there, right?" She points to the door that leads to the pinball workshop.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I won't, sir..." She exhales, shaking visibly. Then she collects herself.
Kim Kitsuragi: He puts the handcuffs away. "These won't be necessary. I will take you to Station 57 myself -- and slow the extradition process as much as I can."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It may be possible to stall it indefinitely. But you *will* be safer there for the purposes of this investigation." He turns to you.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "After that I sort of..." She smiles. "Transitioned out of the whole culture scene."
Volition: It looks like this one's not waking up. You'll have to do it without pushing her further. At least for now.
Physical Instrument: Wait, wait, everyone -- just *wait*. What is this? Derail this whole thing immediately and *investigate*.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You've been trying to kick that door down, right?" She points to the barred door, next to the window. "Maybe it leads downstairs?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She could have had access to the roof." She points to the barred door next to the window. "You've noticed that door there, right? Maybe it leads downstairs?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "How do you deal with anything? It's all just..." She looks at you with pleading eyes. "How do *you* do it?"
Volition: Nothing to do with her? You'll be the judge of that.
Inland Empire: She's already in prison here. For what happened. And she is prepared to never leave. Even after his death.
Volition: I can't restrain this one. The need to *cop* is too strong. You just need to ask it.
Volition: There is something suspicious about that theory, but you can't put your finger on it.
You: "It's okay if you did it in self defence."
You: "Would you say she is... the eighth Hardie boy?"
Empathy: The conference centres... the people who are angry at her. Her past.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I am not. There is more here, miss."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I sense you're being sarcastic. Okay. The thing is -- you're on the payroll of the Moralist International..." She stops to fish a new cigarette out of the pack.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "As to who hired me for the job -- I don't know. But *they're* after me too. Along with Looskap, and their friends in the MI." She breathes out, heavily. "Once you're done in the competitive intelligence circuit, you don't have allies. You're radioactive."
You: "I think we're done here -- for now." (Conclude.)

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "He was heavy. I pushed him off and he fell to the floor -- there." She points through the window. "He only had his boots on. I bit the pillow... not to scream, then ran downstairs..." There's a long pause. She just stands there, her arms at her sides.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I waited for the second shot to come -- for me. I thought there would be one. It never came."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "He was still on the floor. Slouched. I couldn't be there with him anymore. So I ran down -- and out of my room. Into the hallway. Down the stairs. I knew there would be people there."
Empathy: Run, woman! Run past them and out into the street where it's dark and people move -- to the lorries at the intersection. As far as you can...
Drama: You *may* sometimes be bad at reading her, but this time, truly -- she's telling you how it really went down.
Kim Kitsuragi: "To produce lividity matching a hanging?"
Pain Threshold: A great pain moves through her, a dark and indefinite wave. She continues in spite of it.
You: "You don't have to continue if you don't want to."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "That's the first thing that went through my head, when I heard the glass break."
Visual Calculus: This tactful approach will rob you the glory, but hey, all I care about is angles and timetables. The loss is yours.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She nods.
Kim Kitsuragi: "About half an hour had passed since the moment of death?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I've said I'm sorry. What more do you want me to say? I did my best not to lie. It didn't always work."
Visual Calculus: You should have a look at that window -- reconstruct the scene. It's right here, so near...
Suggestion: Try not to sweat so profusely in her presence too. You'll blow your chances.
Drama: Seditious talk! That was not even Our Wise Council, it was this shithead! This one. The next one.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "A teenage boy. A million years ago."
You: "Wait, Klaasje is an abbreviation of Katarzine Alasije?"
Drama: Okay, he's too busy doing something else now. I meant Rhetoric. Anyway, don't listen to that guy -- we're right, she's saintly. Carry on.
You: "Kim, arrest this woman before she can say anything else." (Ignore her theory.)
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Okay." She looks relieved.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "The peephole. My bed is right next to..." She's forgotten her cigarette in the ash tray. "She would have seen us."
Savoir Faire: Then slipped back downstairs without anyone noticing? That *is* possible...
Volition: That's it. I'm calling it. Kim is beyond compromised.
You: "I don't know what to make of this."
You: "I do like the sound of that... another Revachol. Free. Independent."
You: "Let's write you a Station Call. If you miss it -- I can't help you anymore." (Write a Station Call.)
"Let's write you a Station Call, Katarzine. If you miss it -- I can't help you anymore." (Write a Station Call.)
"Let's write you a Station Call, Klaasje. If you miss it -- I can't help you anymore." (Write a Station Call.)
"Let's write you a Station Call, Miss Oranje. If you miss it -- I can't help you anymore." (Write a Station Call.)
Drama: If you have doubts, just give us *one* example of deceit! Just one, and we will gladly change our minds.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Okay." She puts her coffee mug on the table.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Before we do..." He turns to her, the cuffs still in his hand. "What exactly in your relationship made you think she's romantically interested in you?"

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She said she's in love with me. She even asked me to run away with her, when I told her I'm a fugitive. She started developing... *notions* about our relationship."

Electrochemistry: No, wait! Look at her! Teeth like pearls, face like a pebble -- she looks like a Twenties movie star. You can almost see her in Automatik Polychrome. Those posters in Ruby's lorry...
You: "I've made my choice." (Decide what to do with her.)
Electrochemistry: Look at her: teeth like pearls, face like a pebble -- she looks like a Twenties movie star. You can almost see her in Automatik Polychrome. Those posters in Ruby's lorry...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "You answer to the Coalition Government -- and, by extension, the *Moralintern*..." She reaches for a new cigarette.
Composure: Just like that. No resistance -- her shoulders are slouched, her feet long and straight.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She could have come up through there, then taken the shot -- right here, where I stand. It was too dark outside, I wouldn't have seen her."
Volition: Here we go. For once you seem to have her off-guard.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): The young woman looks at her cigarette -- with melancholy. It's almost gone.
Empathy: That can wait. Look into her eyes -- there's more.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No -- not just yet." He turns to the woman. "Who is *Ruby*?"
You: "The RCM isn't the lapdog of the Moralintern. You don't have to worry."
Jump to: [You: ""Before we continue -- who is Ruby?""]
You: "Before we continue -- who is Ruby?"
Suggestion: It could have been a *desire* murder. Maybe an act of jealousy?
You: "You don't look surprised. You were expecting this."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I knew there was a chance you'd get them to tell you. It's what you do. You're the police."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I know that. But the people around here -- they don't see it that way. And if I am to stay here I need to get along with them."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Officer. Regain control of yourself." He turns to the woman: "What does our *limited cooperation* with the Moralintern have to do with this?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She nods. "You share a database with them. You send people to their courts." She lights the cigarette.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happens if they do?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "They will kill me, sir. If you file my name -- take me in for questioning -- enter me into the Moralintern mill..."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I don't." She shrugs. "How do *you* live with yourself?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "That's okay." He makes a note. "Were you inebriated?"
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Not as much as usual. He'd done a line. Plus other things. I was drinking."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "It took Ruby maybe half an hour to come back with Titus. I'd gotten him ready by then, they carried him out. I knew what they were going to do -- make it look like a hanging. Ruby said they would."
You: "What did you do while they were hanging him?"
Logic: He was a serviceman. He must have had a gun lying around. Close to her hand -- a military weapon using *jacketed ammunition*.
Drama: Who hath told you these *lies*? She was merely confused by the esoteric arts you deploy in policework.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I don't know. I haven't seen her since."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Thursday night. It was late. Some time after twelve."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods in your direction: "It checks out."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "But I know the *time* of the call too!" She breathes in. "I know I have not been 100% truthful with you, officers. But I *am* now."
Conceptualization: She sounds like a sixth grader, apologizing.
Drama: Welcome to the wake-up club, brother.
You: "We don't need to do this." (Back off.)
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "What?" Her nails tap on the steel railing, nervously. The sound of cold metal ringing under the wind.
You: "I should have guessed. You don't look Oranjese."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I am." Her smile quivers. "They can never take my sash and my sceptre from me."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "That's cool..." She looks at the ashtray. Then up at you.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She nods, her back straight -- ready for whatever is next.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "No." She shrugs it off. "No -- why would she do that to herself? No, I just remembered you told me about it, and..."

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "*Still...*" she says, her voice breaking. "After all this. Sir, please... it's a shitty world and I know I'm shitty too, I know..." Her hand turns into a fist, slowly, crushing the cigarette she's still holding.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "But I don't deserve to be sent to the Moralintern and ground into paste just because I disturbed the *sanctity* of accounting. At some multinational..."
Drama: By god, she's playing him too! Like a fiddle, sire... Who would have known?
You: "West of the boardwalk, in the reeds? I need to check this buoy out." (Accept task.)
"West of the boardwalk, in the reeds? We have to check this buoy out." (Accept task.)
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant makes a note of it.
Volition: This bastion of willpower here -- his watchmen have been sleeping too, you can be absolutely certain now. But he's coming around.
Perception (Hearing): A little whimper. The young woman hears you. She's looking around.
You: "And *how* could she have killed him?"
Volition: It's ominous -- you buying into her theory and running with it. Be careful with this Logic guy.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Somehow she *knew* Lely was dead. She wasn't surprised at all. When we came up here she was calm as a stone too. She cleaned it all up, like she had a... plan."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "She could have come to the roof through that, then made the shot right here, where I stand. It was dark outside, I wouldn't have seen her."
Authority: Don't arrest her. Push her a bit more but then let her off. That Ruby theory was solid. (And she's beautiful.)
Savoir Faire: She's stuck here. She's already in prison -- look around! She's only trying to help you...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She looks at you in silence, her face filled with fear, lips parted...
You: "Alright. Tell me as much as you're comfortable with."
Electrochemistry: Good thinking. Clear your head. You should clear *your* head... get into his mindset.
Logic: I don't understand what you're doing detective -- *go on*? A new name just emerged -- Ruby! This is important. Change the question immediately.
You: "Why *did* you waste my time then? If you knew I would find out."
Visual Calculus: A grand expanse of water reaches over the bay and to the horizon. Golden grey in the noon light...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I do that too, yes. It's unbelievably effective. Especially when combined with cigarettes. And drugs."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "The Hardie boys," she says as if it's self-evident.
You: "The occult vision was right. He was enjoying the moment of his death."
Reaction Speed: Wait-- the Hardie boys said she'd visited them last week. Glen and...

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I thought officers in Revachol would be more enlightened about these things." She looks you in the eye. "Especially since you've admitted to taking drugs yourself."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Because I'm under stress." Her mouth is tense, the muscles in her feet tighten.

Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "He kept throwing stones at him for *three days*. I could hear the *thud*, *thud*..." She shakes her head. "So I called you. I hope with all my heart it's not the last thing I do in Revachol."
Drama: She definitely called the cops. That was *task complete*. It could not hath been a *lie*. That is impossible.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): She nods, silently. She doesn't even smoke, just picks up the cold coffee and holds it in her hands.
Visual Calculus: You should have another look at that window after this -- reconstruct the scene. It's right there.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I don't..." She squints. "How did you know that?"
You: "I knew he enjoyed the moment he died. I could see it in him."
You: I remember doubting she made the call she said she made. To the police.
Drama: There iseth no doubt! The laedy could not bear the sight of her lover splayed and disfigured. A horrible story.
You: Just a proposition: *Could* the lurid explicitness conceal something less sensational, but more... *illegal*?
Drama: Your paranoia is unflattering. She has been nothing but forthcoming and you're staring mutely into her face like a donkey!
Rhetoric: Who, me? The lady is saintly, oh she sucks on the cigarette most elegantly. Stop staring, you look mentally handicapped.
You: "You're probably not even Miss Oranje '37, are you?"
Conceptualization: Could it mean *Klaasje* is an allacronym? For Katarzine Alasije?
Electrochemistry: Of course -- she doesn't look like an Oranjese woman at all. She's...
Visual Calculus: The grand expanse of water is barely visible in the darkness of the night. The horizon is there, somewhere...
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Who was he? A boy. A student. It was a good thing and I destroyed him." She looks you in the eye, her mouth quivering.
"He was a writer, he made Oranjese lit -- and I destroyed him." She looks you in the eye, her mouth quivering.
